<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm361128336"><term>product life cycle</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm362147232">The pattern of sales and profits over time for a product or product category; consists of an introductory stage, growth stage, maturity, and decline (and death).</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>

